Transform Data 8

In the query editor, carry out these steps:

Click on remove rows, type 1 in the box to remover the title.
In transform tab, click on use first row as headers.
In home tab, click on choose columns.
There are 115 columns. Choose the columns as indicated in the gif.




Go to close & apply, click close & apply to import data into the model

Learn more on cleaning of data from https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/learn/modules/clean-data-power-bi/
